vfetch
=====

A FastFetch-like system information tool built with V and Nim interoperability.

vfetch is a command-line system information tool that displays system information with ASCII art logos, similar to FastFetch. It demonstrates V-Nim interoperability by combining V for system information gathering and Nim for image/ASCII art rendering.

Features:
- Displays system information (OS, kernel, uptime, packages, shell, DE/WM, CPU, GPU, memory, disk, network)
- Shows ASCII art logo
- Fast and lightweight

Usage:
Simply run 'vfetch' to display system information.